body:
The generated model has a Relu node whose input (sequential/dense/BiasAdd:0) is of type double. We have implemented only float support for Relu. If you enable verbose logging you'll see this error message: "2020-01-10 18:33:16.3760603 [I:onnxruntime:Default, kernel_registry.cc:273 onnxruntime::KernelRegistry::TryFindKernel] Relu kernel is not supported in CPUExecutionProvider Encountered following errors: (Op: Relu Incompatible types. )". 

Can you use float instead of double? 

-----
node {
  input: "sequential/dense/BiasAdd:0"
  output: "sequential/dense/Relu:0"
  name: "sequential/dense/Relu"
  op_type: "Relu"
}

initializer {
  dims: 10
  data_type: 11
  name: "sequential/dense_1/BiasAdd/ReadVariableOp/_2__cf__2:0"
  raw_data: "\352\t\001\177\330o\263\277_\0322u[\022\234?\217\371r\234\356GZ?\263g\031BP\225\237\277\236\2705\374\313an\277\217H\234\323\321\260\227?\325\216y|\242\224\220\277\024\237-#\316\216\263?\007\325\024?\205#\240\277\274[l\343\274)\206?"
}

Do you know how I could use floats? Putting `tf.keras.backend.set_floatx('float32')` before defining the model still gives the same error.

Also what is the syntax for enabling verbose logging? `sess_options.session_log_verbosity_level` gives an error.

> Also what is the syntax for enabling verbose logging? `sess_options.session_log_verbosity_level` gives an error.
```
import onnxruntime as ort
ort.set_default_logger_severity(0)
```

Thanks, any ideas about overwriting the default use of doubles with floats?

> data_type: 11

Does this attribute need to be set to a different integer?

Using https://www.tensorflow.org/api_docs/python/tf/keras/backend/set_floatx should've worked. Not sure why it's not working. May be try on keras github.
Regarding the data_type attribute, you don't have to set it manually; it's taken care of as part of the conversion process.
